  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "A university-affiliated program that translates agricultural and horticultural research into practical guidance for the public. Cooperative extension services exist in every U.S. state and many other countries under different names. They publish regionally specific growing guides, perform soil testing, and provide advice based on local conditions. They are among the most reliable sources of gardening information for a specific area.\n",
